annotations: Hi, my name is Janice Cupp and I am a very recent transplant from Hawaii. After nine years

away from California we are back ﬁnally. I have two grown children and have been married for over 30 yrs to my best friend. You will see I have a lengthy resume and have had many jobs in the past due to my husbands company. However he will retire here in Fresno no more moves and I am looking to put down some roots here in Fresno. I am hard working and always excel wherever I am. I look forward to hearing from you. EXPERIENCE

I was hired on as a personal shopper for the holidays and greatly enjoyed that, it was fast paced and just a really great environment. I did not stay on after the holidays. I had many family members come to stay for the last few months of my stay in Hawaii. The goal was to enjoy it while we were there. Our store director is Robert and he can be reached at 808-***-****

I was responsible for the tracking of sold high end items and keeping the case stocked and serving guests as they came in. This was also fast paced. It was located in the tourist area of Fort Lauderdale Florida. At the time we moved to Hawaii I was in the training process for the cash ofﬁce. My Store leader here was Jermaine and he may be reached at 954-***-****

I was hired on as a cashier and worked my way up to an HR assistant and was responsible for a number of tasks. Keeping and maintaining our time keeping system. Hiring and on boarding all new employees. Answering all beneﬁts related questions. Party planning, ofﬁce supply chain management. The upkeep of all our handheld devises utilized in-store. Including downloading all new programs. I ﬁelded calls for the ofﬁce and maintained our break room. We moved to Florida in 2018. The Store Team Lead here is Alana Ruvolo and she may be reached at

I started out as a housekeeper for the hospital in Roseville CA and quickly worked my way up to an ofﬁce job as the purchasing clerk for the operating room. My tasks were plenty. I was responsible for all the surgical billing and maintenance of those records. I procured all the skin grafts and bone tissue and medical equipment for upcoming surgeries. A job I JANICE KAY CUPP
would have never left but my husbands company took us to Michigan. The head of my dept is Kevin McGoldrick and he may be reached at 916-***-**** EDUCATION

I am a master at being able to learn relatively quickly any program as I did in my HR position. No training there I had to learn all on my own. What I don’t know I ﬁgure out. I’m a doer for sure and I love people.
I am providing three references of none family members Carol Brooks 209-***-****
